6. Why this matters for plasma and fusion

Fusion reactors fail because of turbulence.

Tiny magnetic instabilities cause:
	•	energy leaks
	•	plasma disruptions
	•	reactor shutdowns

If we could monitor braid complexity, we might predict instability earlier.

Some experimental diagnostics are already exploring this.

